BARBERTON &#8211; General Street in front of the municipal building in Umjindi was absolute chaos this morning when students from various schools in Emjindini were taken from their classes by members of the community, without their consent.The Barberton circuit manager from the Department of Education, Thoko Khoza, who was also on scene, said that she is in the dark as to what the cause of the unrest was.She was contacted by principals who informed her that their students were not safe. She added that she cannot give a formal statement because she is currently only assessing the situation.&#8220;The safety of the learners is more important than any other thing,&#8221; she said.The police and traffic department are still monitoring the situation.&nbsp;